    "intro": "Interpretation moves from what the text says to what the author intends and what the text means within the canon. Esther 8 is the theological and narrative climax of the book — the reversal that chapters 1-7 have been building toward. The four movements below trace the argument from the legal problem through its resolution to its eschatological resonance. The book never mentions God's name, but the movements below show why that silence does not indicate His absence.",
